    <title>WADL Files</title>
    <para>Writers and developers at Rackspace and in the OpenStack
        community use Web Application Description Language (WADL)
        files to describe HTTP-based Web applications and generate
        displayable API reference information.</para>


    <para>This chapter helps you: <itemizedlist>

            <listitem>
                <para>Create WADL files to describe HTTP-based Web
                    applications.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Understand the API reference outputs that you
                    can generate from WADL files.</para>
                <para>These outputs include roll-up tables, detailed
                    API reference information, and API reference
                    pages. </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Generate displayable API reference outputs from
                    embedded WADL files. </para>



                <para>To do so, you mark up your DocBook XML files to
                    include some or all methods in one or more WADL
                    files. To generate rollup tables, you also use the
                        <literal>role="api-reference"</literal>
                    attribute on a <literal>chapter</literal> or
                        <literal>section</literal> element.</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist></para>
    <note>
        <para>Rackspace developers and writers also use WADL files to
            configure Repose. This chapter does not cover this
            topic.</para>
    </note>
    <para>For complete information about the WADL language, see <link
            xlink:href="http://www.w3.org/Submission/wadl/">Web
            Application Description Language</link>. The information
        in this chapter comes from that document. </para>


    <section xml:id="create_wadl">
