        <calloutlist>
            <callout arearefs="test.wadl.base">
                <para>base attribute</para>
                <para>Provides the base URI for each child resource
                    ID. </para>
            </callout>
            <callout arearefs="test.wadl.resource">
                <para><emphasis role="bold">resource</emphasis></para>
                <para>Describes a resource provided by the
                    application. Each resource is identified by a URI
                    that follows a common pattern. A resource element
                    has the following attributes:</para>
                <calloutlist>
                    <callout arearefs="test.wadl.id">
                        <para><emphasis role="bold"
                            >id</emphasis></para>
                        <para>Optional. Attribute of type xsd:ID that
                            identifies the resource element. </para>
                    </callout>
                    <callout arearefs="test.wadl.path">
                        <para><code>path</code>. An optional attribute
                            of type xsd:string. If present, it
                            provides a relative URI template for the
                            identifier of the resource. The resource's
                            base URI is given by the resource
                            element's parent resource or resources
                            element. </para>
                    </callout>
                    <callout arearefs="test.wadl.type">
                        <para><code>type</code></para>
                        <para>An optional attribute whose type is a
                            space-separated list of of xsd:anyURI.
                            Each value in the list is a cross
                            reference that identifies a resource_type
                            element that defines a set of methods
                            supported by the resource. </para>
                    </callout>

                </calloutlist>

                <para>A resource element contains the following child
                    elements: <calloutlist>

                        <callout arearefs="test.wadl.param">
                            <para>param</para>
                            <para>Zero or more <code>param</code>
                                elements (see section 2.12 ) with one
                                of the following values for its style
                                attribute: </para>
                            <para><code>template</code>. Provides
                                additional information about an
                                embedded template parameter, see
                                above. Child param elements whose name
                                attribute value does not match the
                                name of an embedded template parameter
                                are ignored. </para>
                            <para><code>matrix</code>. Specifies a
                                matrix URI parameter </para>
                            <para><code>query</code>. Specifies a
                                global URI query parameter All child
                                method elements of the resource. Does
                                not apply to methods inherited from a
                                resource_type specified using the type
                                attribute. </para>
                            <para><code>header</code>. Specifies a
                                global HTTP header for use in the
                                request part of all child method
                                elements of the resource. Does not
                                apply to methods inherited from a
                                resource_type specified using the type
                                attribute. </para>
                        </callout>
                        <callout arearefs="test.wadl.method">
                            <para>method</para>
                            <para>Zero or more <code>method</code>
                                elements, each of which describes the
                                input to and output from an HTTP
                                protocol method that can be applied to
                                the resource. Such locally-defined
                                methods are added to any methods
                                included in resource_type elements
                                referred to using the type attribute.
                            </para>
                        </callout>

                    </calloutlist>
                </para>

            </callout>
        </calloutlist>
